dc_title_s: Orange Quadrangle, New Jersey. 7.5 minute series (topographic)
dc_description_s: U.S.G.S. 7.5 minute series (topographic) North Decimal Degree 40.875000. South Decimal Degree 40.750000. East Decimal Degree -74.125000. West Decimal Degree -74.250000. Alternate title: Orange, NJ. Polyconic projection. Universal transverse Mercator grids are shown. Relief shown by 20 feet contour interval and spot heights. Datum is mean sea level. Depth curves and soundings in feet- datum is mean low water. Shoreline shown represents the approximate line of mean high water. The mean range of tide is approximately 5.1 feet. "Mapped by the Army Map Service; edited, and published by the United States Geological Survey. Control by USGS, USC&GS, USCE, and New Jersey Geodetic Survey. Topography from aerial photographs by photogrammetric methods. Aerial photographs taken 1942 and 1943. Field check 1943. Culture revised by the USGS by planetable surveys 1955." Map is temporarily filed in the Reserve Course Materials Collection.
